1
00:00:02,570 --> 00:00:06,340
Did you already see
what you are standing next to?

2
00:00:09,343 --> 00:00:11,379
YOSHIO LOVES MANCHICHI

3
00:00:12,380 --> 00:00:14,048
My feelings have not changed since then.

4
00:00:16,617 --> 00:00:21,222
I still love you.

5
00:00:34,802 --> 00:00:38,439
I don't love you.

6
00:00:40,207 --> 00:00:43,744
I knew you'd say that, Manchichi.

7
00:00:44,845 --> 00:00:49,083
I don't intend to break up your happiness

8
00:00:49,450 --> 00:00:51,519
or to interfere with it either.

9
00:00:53,287 --> 00:00:59,326
However, I will continue
to challenge you, Manchichi,

10
00:01:00,027 --> 00:01:02,296
with this true love of mine.

11
00:01:02,763 --> 00:01:03,664
Challenge?

12
00:01:04,198 --> 00:01:05,166
Yes.

13
00:01:07,635 --> 00:01:09,236
I don't get it at all,

14
00:01:10,137 --> 00:01:11,639
but do as you wish.

15
00:01:18,179 --> 00:01:21,115
Oh, I feel better now.
I don't have a moment to waste.

16
00:01:32,026 --> 00:01:35,629
The identity of Kenji Rusudo,
the beautiful realtor prince

17
00:01:35,796 --> 00:01:38,699
who suddenly appeared, was revealed.

18
00:01:38,866 --> 00:01:43,270
And Machi and Yashiro's marriage
slowly starts to crumble.

19
00:01:47,107 --> 00:01:49,743
Oh, what is love?

20
00:01:54,181 --> 00:01:55,616
Manager!

21
00:01:55,783 --> 00:01:56,684
Shirasu!

22
00:01:56,851 --> 00:01:58,486
What are you doing here?

23
00:01:58,652 --> 00:01:59,887
What are you doing here?

24
00:02:00,054 --> 00:02:03,090
Can't you tell? I work here part-time now.

25
00:02:03,991 --> 00:02:09,029
Hey, Manager! What's up?
You look so pathetic all alone.

26
00:02:09,563 --> 00:02:13,467
Are you perhaps facing
the possibility of a divorce?

27
00:02:13,634 --> 00:02:15,236
It's not like that at all.

28
00:02:15,402 --> 00:02:18,472
But even when you go home,
Sanchi isn't there, right?

29
00:02:20,074 --> 00:02:24,812
I always knew the marriage between
you and Sanchi would be difficult.

30
00:02:24,979 --> 00:02:26,780
Like I said, it's not like that at all.

31
00:02:26,947 --> 00:02:28,849
Ms. Shirasu, are you done lining
up the products?

32
00:02:29,016 --> 00:02:33,687
I ran into my boss from when I was
a business woman, so we were chatting.

33
00:02:33,854 --> 00:02:37,258
It seems that his marriage
is not going well.

34
00:02:37,958 --> 00:02:39,827
Go and get the products out already!

35
00:02:39,994 --> 00:02:41,362
Oh, Manager,

36
00:02:41,529 --> 00:02:43,898
this is Ms. Misato, the store manager.

37
00:02:44,064 --> 00:02:45,566
Thank you for your business.

38
00:02:45,733 --> 00:02:48,502
Oh, hello. Thank you
for looking after Shirasu.

39
00:02:48,669 --> 00:02:49,837
Excuse me.

40
00:02:50,004 --> 00:02:52,540
Where are the heat packs
you stick onto socks?

41
00:02:52,706 --> 00:02:53,641
Heat packs?

42
00:02:54,642 --> 00:02:58,479
Where could it be?
Heat packs, huh? Where is it?

43
00:02:59,480 --> 00:03:01,215
I wonder if she's going to get
it together.

44
00:03:05,185 --> 00:03:06,020
Do you have a cold?

45
00:03:06,186 --> 00:03:07,388
Just a little.

46
00:03:07,922 --> 00:03:09,390
When you have a cold…

47
00:03:11,191 --> 00:03:13,994
This is very effective.

48
00:03:15,763 --> 00:03:19,066
It really warms you up.
Please give it a try.

49
00:03:19,433 --> 00:03:21,135
Ginger Kudzu drink?

50
00:03:22,069 --> 00:03:23,771
It'll warm you up.

51
00:03:26,173 --> 00:03:27,341
It'll warm me up?

52
00:03:28,175 --> 00:03:29,944
TEIKO REAL ESTATE

53
00:03:30,811 --> 00:03:31,946
Um…

54
00:03:33,314 --> 00:03:37,918
I've been meaning to ask you since
I woke up this morning…

55
00:03:38,385 --> 00:03:39,486
What is it?

56
00:03:41,021 --> 00:03:43,223
What time did you come home last night?

57
00:03:43,390 --> 00:03:44,558
Around four.

58
00:03:44,992 --> 00:03:48,329
What were you doing out till so late?

59
00:03:50,297 --> 00:03:51,932
I was working.

60
00:03:52,099 --> 00:03:53,901
-Alone?
-Yes.

61
00:03:54,068 --> 00:03:54,969
What work?

62
00:03:55,135 --> 00:03:57,271
Selling properties.

63
00:04:00,641 --> 00:04:01,542
Welcome.

64
00:04:02,910 --> 00:04:05,112
What? You're Minato!

65
00:04:06,680 --> 00:04:09,917
Don't yell out the customer's name.
I apologize.

66
00:04:10,250 --> 00:04:12,286
Mr. Niwano, don't you know?

67
00:04:12,519 --> 00:04:17,625
This is Minato, the charismatic
hair stylist who cuts celebrities' hair!

68
00:04:17,791 --> 00:04:20,527
Do not point! Leave! Go!

69
00:04:20,995 --> 00:04:22,563
Don't do that.

70
00:04:23,864 --> 00:04:25,232
We apologize.

71
00:04:25,399 --> 00:04:28,669
Well, I'm used to being referred to as
"Minato", so it's fine.

72
00:04:28,836 --> 00:04:31,772
We're both hair stylists. Minato is
in charge of the first location,

73
00:04:31,939 --> 00:04:33,374
and I'm in charge of the second.

74
00:04:33,774 --> 00:04:36,977
I see. Now, you mentioned
on the phone the other day

75
00:04:37,444 --> 00:04:40,547
that you want a home
that will bring good Feng Shui,

76
00:04:40,714 --> 00:04:42,082
so I've found a few.

77
00:04:42,449 --> 00:04:47,721
This property we found is located
southeast of your current home.

78
00:04:48,288 --> 00:04:49,657
Southeast is a lucky direction,

79
00:04:49,823 --> 00:04:51,792
both in fortune telling and in Feng Shui.

80
00:04:52,292 --> 00:04:55,095
It is known as the direction where
business thrives!

81
00:04:59,199 --> 00:05:01,068
This front door is facing southeast,

82
00:05:01,235 --> 00:05:04,938
and the shoe storage is on the right,
and the mirror is on the left.

83
00:05:05,305 --> 00:05:08,909
It's an octagonal mirror that brings
in happiness and rejects evil.

84
00:05:09,076 --> 00:05:11,912
I like the mirror to be
in front of me though.

85
00:05:12,079 --> 00:05:13,547
That is not good.

86
00:05:13,714 --> 00:05:17,618
A mirror directly in front
of an entrance will reject luck.

87
00:05:17,785 --> 00:05:19,186
You know a lot.

88
00:05:19,586 --> 00:05:21,188
I'm a realtor.

89
00:05:22,856 --> 00:05:25,659
This living room faces east.

90
00:05:25,993 --> 00:05:29,830
In terms of Feng Shui, east-facing
living rooms bring in information,

91
00:05:29,997 --> 00:05:32,900
making your luck active and energetic.

92
00:05:33,434 --> 00:05:36,070
The entrance facing southeast,
and the living room facing east,

93
00:05:36,236 --> 00:05:38,605
will mean your business is sure
to thrive even more.

94
00:05:39,173 --> 00:05:42,142
The general rule is that
south-facing homes are better.

95
00:05:42,643 --> 00:05:43,777
I don't mean to be rude,

96
00:05:43,944 --> 00:05:48,082
but both of you work at your salon
during the daytime.

97
00:05:48,248 --> 00:05:52,052
I think it's of more value when you
get sunlight in the morning.

98
00:05:52,219 --> 00:05:53,554
I see.

99
00:05:53,721 --> 00:05:57,958
When TV and other electronics
are placed east, the effect multiplies.

100
00:06:05,099 --> 00:06:07,634
We know you requested a two bedroom house.

101
00:06:08,001 --> 00:06:09,903
Will this be used as a guest bedroom?

102
00:06:10,070 --> 00:06:14,108
No, that's not it.
We need separate bedrooms.

103
00:06:14,274 --> 00:06:17,211
We're married but we are
business partners and friends.

104
00:06:20,647 --> 00:06:24,485
The two bedrooms are both on
the northwest side.

105
00:06:25,052 --> 00:06:28,021
Northwest is the direction for
a king and a CEO,

106
00:06:28,589 --> 00:06:31,091
so if you sleep with your head
facing the northwest…

107
00:06:31,658 --> 00:06:33,293
Then what…?

108
00:06:33,460 --> 00:06:37,064
Mr. Minato will flourish even more
as a charismatic stylist,

109
00:06:37,231 --> 00:06:41,635
and ma'am, you will succeed
as a business owner!

110
00:06:42,536 --> 00:06:45,572
If possible, the curtain should be gold.

111
00:06:45,739 --> 00:06:48,675
That's amazing. You could be
a certified Feng Shui master.

112
00:06:48,842 --> 00:06:50,844
I am a realtor.

113
00:06:51,678 --> 00:06:55,449
This place is really nice,
but could we think about it a bit?

114
00:06:55,616 --> 00:06:57,184
It is a little above our budget…

115
00:06:57,351 --> 00:07:02,055
Feng Shui is used to direct
a country to its eternal prosperity.

116
00:07:02,322 --> 00:07:06,560
Living in this Feng Shui perfect home
will prosper your business,

117
00:07:06,727 --> 00:07:10,931
so the fact that it's above your budget
will be nothing.

118
00:07:11,098 --> 00:07:12,199
Nothing?

119
00:07:12,633 --> 00:07:14,835
Well, we are not planning to have kids,

120
00:07:15,002 --> 00:07:18,939
and it's our number-one dream
to do well with our salons.

121
00:07:19,773 --> 00:07:21,241
This house is good for us, Minato!

122
00:07:21,408 --> 00:07:25,145
Well, if it's "nothing" then I guess
I'll apply for it.

123
00:07:25,946 --> 00:07:29,016
-Niwano! Application form!
-Yes!

124
00:07:31,418 --> 00:07:32,619
Thank you very much.

125
00:07:32,786 --> 00:07:33,754
Thank you.

126
00:07:36,156 --> 00:07:38,759
You sure are good, Chief.
They went for it.

127
00:07:38,926 --> 00:07:41,195
-You don't know that yet.
-What?

128
00:07:41,595 --> 00:07:42,863
See you! I'm going this way!

129
00:07:44,298 --> 00:07:46,700
-Oh?
-Follow the husband.

130
00:07:46,867 --> 00:07:48,035
For what?

131
00:07:48,202 --> 00:07:49,670
It's to sell a house!

132
00:07:49,837 --> 00:07:52,806
-But if they find out, the deal--
-If he sees you, use this.

133
00:07:53,841 --> 00:07:55,943
Tell him you came to deliver
what they left behind.

134
00:07:56,109 --> 00:07:57,711
This is his wife's umbrella, right?

135
00:07:58,178 --> 00:08:02,216
I will talk to the wife who will probably
come back for that umbrella.

136
00:08:02,382 --> 00:08:03,550
Okay…

137
00:08:04,051 --> 00:08:06,420
-Go right now, go!
-Yes!

138
00:08:17,631 --> 00:08:18,599
Mari!

139
00:08:20,133 --> 00:08:21,735
-Good morning.
-Minato!

140
00:08:21,902 --> 00:08:23,437
-Sorry to make you wait.
-Not at all.

141
00:08:23,604 --> 00:08:25,339
-You look really cute.
-Really?

142
00:08:25,505 --> 00:08:26,373
Different hair color?

143
00:08:26,540 --> 00:08:28,208
This is what you did the other day.

144
00:08:28,375 --> 00:08:29,509
It looks really good on you.

145
00:08:35,883 --> 00:08:39,519
What? Ouch! Ouch!

146
00:08:39,686 --> 00:08:41,288
Are you okay?

147
00:08:42,122 --> 00:08:43,323
Ouch…

148
00:08:44,424 --> 00:08:47,995
Oh? You are that…

149
00:08:48,896 --> 00:08:50,898
You left this.

150
00:08:51,064 --> 00:08:53,967
Ah, my wife's umbrella.

151
00:08:57,237 --> 00:08:59,406
Don't look so uncomfortable.

152
00:08:59,673 --> 00:09:03,510
This is Ms. Mari Oda,
and my wife is aware of this.

153
00:09:09,449 --> 00:09:11,818
I think I left my umbrella here.

154
00:09:11,985 --> 00:09:16,123
My subordinate has taken your umbrella
to your husband.

155
00:09:16,290 --> 00:09:18,558
Oh, I see. Thank you then.

156
00:09:18,725 --> 00:09:23,263
Ma'am, if you are not in a rush,
I would like to know

157
00:09:23,430 --> 00:09:25,866
how you two divide your personal
private lives within your marriage?

158
00:09:26,033 --> 00:09:28,168
I already signed the application form.

159
00:09:28,335 --> 00:09:30,437
I don't mean it that way,
but as a realtor,

160
00:09:30,604 --> 00:09:34,274
I would like to learn different
forms of marriage.

161
00:09:34,441 --> 00:09:36,443
But if you can't, that's fine.

162
00:09:40,480 --> 00:09:43,083
My husband and I worked
together at a salon.

163
00:09:43,250 --> 00:09:44,651
We fell in love and got married.

164
00:09:45,519 --> 00:09:49,356
We still get along, and we
care a great deal about each other.

165
00:09:49,723 --> 00:09:52,259
But caring for each other

166
00:09:52,426 --> 00:09:55,929
and being a man and a woman
are different things.

167
00:09:56,096 --> 00:09:59,633
You are husband and wife, but you
are not a man and a woman?

168
00:09:59,800 --> 00:10:00,634
Right.

169
00:10:01,735 --> 00:10:07,074
I think many couples stay
in love their whole life,

170
00:10:07,240 --> 00:10:08,141
but that's not it for us.

171
00:10:08,809 --> 00:10:09,676
I see.

172
00:10:09,843 --> 00:10:11,378
Ms. Sangenya, are you married?

173
00:10:11,545 --> 00:10:15,248
I am. For now, we regard
each other as man and woman.

174
00:10:16,450 --> 00:10:17,651
That is nice.

175
00:10:17,818 --> 00:10:18,819
Yes, it is.

176
00:10:19,619 --> 00:10:22,556
We are done with that feeling
of being in romantic love.

177
00:10:23,357 --> 00:10:27,995
I think it's impossible
for both my husband and I

178
00:10:28,161 --> 00:10:29,963
not to fall in love for the rest
of our lives.

179
00:10:30,130 --> 00:10:31,031
I see.

180
00:10:32,165 --> 00:10:35,869
It's a bit creepy to have a husband
that only has eyes for me,

181
00:10:36,303 --> 00:10:39,006
and since I work, I meet people too.

182
00:10:39,473 --> 00:10:44,611
I think it's a waste to hold back
the feeling of a fluttering heart.

183
00:10:45,112 --> 00:10:45,946
Oh…

184
00:10:46,113 --> 00:10:49,783
So my husband and I talked and agreed that
we will love each other as individuals,

185
00:10:49,950 --> 00:10:51,952
and we will stay and grow old together,

186
00:10:52,119 --> 00:10:55,155
but we can fall in love freely
outside of our home.

187
00:10:55,322 --> 00:10:56,323
I see.

188
00:10:56,723 --> 00:10:59,359
My husband became even more charming
when he fell in love,

189
00:10:59,526 --> 00:11:02,195
and when I have a boyfriend,
he tells me that I'm beautiful.

190
00:11:02,462 --> 00:11:05,098
So you both have your lovers right now?

191
00:11:05,265 --> 00:11:06,299
My husband has one.

192
00:11:07,334 --> 00:11:11,138
I had one till recently, but we broke up.

193
00:11:11,638 --> 00:11:13,507
I'm taking a break from love for now.

194
00:11:13,940 --> 00:11:15,642
So you take a break from it too?

195
00:11:16,276 --> 00:11:18,445
Well, it can't just be anyone.

196
00:11:18,845 --> 00:11:19,746
I see.

197
00:11:21,314 --> 00:11:23,550
My husband and I are the same age,

198
00:11:23,717 --> 00:11:26,153
but I actually prefer older men.

199
00:11:26,586 --> 00:11:28,488
I'd like to meet a nice older man.

200
00:11:28,922 --> 00:11:30,824
Thank you for telling me all that.

201
00:11:31,391 --> 00:11:33,160
It was very educational.

202
00:11:34,227 --> 00:11:38,298
They are about to buy a house,
the biggest purchase of their life,

203
00:11:38,465 --> 00:11:41,601
but the charismatic hair-stylist husband
is having an affair,

204
00:11:41,768 --> 00:11:43,470
and the wife accepts it too!

205
00:11:43,637 --> 00:11:45,839
Minato is a serious manji.

206
00:11:46,006 --> 00:11:48,875
-It's a moral crisis.
-It really is.

207
00:11:49,042 --> 00:11:50,877
By the way Tokoshima,
what's "serious manji"?

208
00:11:51,044 --> 00:11:51,978
There's no meaning to it.

209
00:11:52,145 --> 00:11:57,084
And on top of that, his big chested
girlfriend has a husband too!

210
00:11:57,651 --> 00:11:59,086
They are both having an affair, huh.

211
00:11:59,252 --> 00:12:00,120
Big-chested…

212
00:12:00,287 --> 00:12:04,191
That's ridiculous. What's the point
of being married then?

213
00:12:04,357 --> 00:12:08,762
I guess things like that happen
in this world.

214
00:12:08,929 --> 00:12:10,630
But in that case,

215
00:12:10,797 --> 00:12:14,167
even when they are open about it,
one of them is holding back

216
00:12:14,601 --> 00:12:17,804
or suffering inside.

217
00:12:18,271 --> 00:12:20,240
Yeah, I think so too.

218
00:12:20,407 --> 00:12:23,910
Once I agree with the kind
of relationship the Yasoda couple has,

219
00:12:24,511 --> 00:12:29,249
everything I've believed in until now
will crumble down.

220
00:12:29,783 --> 00:12:33,620
I'm not sure whether that should
be the norm for this society--

221
00:12:33,787 --> 00:12:35,288
That's not relevant.

222
00:12:35,822 --> 00:12:37,491
Oh, welcome back.

223
00:12:37,657 --> 00:12:40,627
Niwano, since when are you a critic
of how a marriage should be?

224
00:12:41,061 --> 00:12:42,395
I'm a realtor.

225
00:12:42,562 --> 00:12:44,264
Then just stick to selling houses.

226
00:12:44,431 --> 00:12:45,298
Well…

227
00:12:45,465 --> 00:12:47,467
That may be,

228
00:12:47,934 --> 00:12:50,303
but I understand how Niwano feels.

229
00:12:50,470 --> 00:12:56,143
I don't think it's bad to use this chance
to discuss our own opinions about this.

230
00:12:56,309 --> 00:12:57,611
That's a useless discussion.

231
00:12:59,946 --> 00:13:02,149
Realtors sell properties.

232
00:13:02,315 --> 00:13:04,684
You are right, but…

233
00:13:07,721 --> 00:13:10,524
There is no property I can't sell.

234
00:13:27,340 --> 00:13:28,441
Here you go.

235
00:13:28,608 --> 00:13:29,509
Thank you.

236
00:13:37,050 --> 00:13:38,518
Enjoy!

237
00:13:40,387 --> 00:13:42,989
You live with your wife?

238
00:13:43,156 --> 00:13:46,326
Yes, and we don't have any kids.

239
00:13:47,260 --> 00:13:51,131
My wife used to be my student,
and she's still young,

240
00:13:51,731 --> 00:13:53,833
so it is possible to have kids.

241
00:13:54,768 --> 00:13:57,404
But I just want the two of us
to enjoy our lives.

242
00:13:58,338 --> 00:14:02,475
If we had kids, then half of my
wife's attention will be taken away.

243
00:14:03,476 --> 00:14:06,846
Maybe I'm the jealous type,

244
00:14:07,180 --> 00:14:09,349
but I want the two of us to focus
on each other forever.

245
00:14:10,150 --> 00:14:11,685
You two sound like a wonderful couple.

246
00:14:12,719 --> 00:14:17,524
Well, this country is experiencing
low childbirth,

247
00:14:18,258 --> 00:14:21,428
so a child-less couple is treated coldly.

248
00:14:21,928 --> 00:14:25,031
I feel bad about making Mari
go through that.

249
00:14:25,198 --> 00:14:28,101
I don't think you have to
be that sensitive.

250
00:14:29,536 --> 00:14:30,470
Thank you.

251
00:14:32,939 --> 00:14:36,109
Your wife's name is Mari?

252
00:14:36,276 --> 00:14:38,745
Yes, her name is "Oda Mari".

253
00:14:39,212 --> 00:14:40,113
Oda Mari!

254
00:14:41,147 --> 00:14:42,415
Isn't that a funny name?

255
00:14:43,250 --> 00:14:46,119
When she got married, her surname changed.

256
00:14:47,754 --> 00:14:49,623
I feel bad about that too.

257
00:14:50,290 --> 00:14:56,730
And lately, my wife's attention
seems elsewhere.

258
00:14:57,931 --> 00:15:02,035
-Elsewhere?
-We've been married for seven years,

259
00:15:02,202 --> 00:15:04,804
I guess things are not so fresh anymore.

260
00:15:05,272 --> 00:15:10,443
So I thought to freshen things up
by moving to a different house.

261
00:15:11,711 --> 00:15:13,113
I understand.

262
00:15:13,713 --> 00:15:17,684
I will look for a home where you
and Mrs. Oda

263
00:15:18,318 --> 00:15:20,153
will feel like when you were newlyweds.

264
00:15:21,288 --> 00:15:23,356
Thank you very much.

265
00:15:24,858 --> 00:15:27,494
Madam, how do you like it?

266
00:15:29,129 --> 00:15:31,298
Oh my! It looks great on you.

267
00:15:31,464 --> 00:15:33,366
It's too big for me.

268
00:15:33,533 --> 00:15:35,802
Oh? Is it a little big?

269
00:15:35,969 --> 00:15:39,339
I asked you to order me a size nine,
but this is size 13.

270
00:15:39,506 --> 00:15:40,807
You made an error.

271
00:15:40,974 --> 00:15:42,976
It's fine. I won't buy this.

272
00:15:45,011 --> 00:15:46,379
What happened?

273
00:15:46,546 --> 00:15:48,815
I ordered the wrong size.

274
00:15:49,482 --> 00:15:53,153
What? Chief Sangenya and Mr. Rusudo
were having a secret meeting?

275
00:15:53,753 --> 00:15:56,523
They used to be classmates
in elementary school.

276
00:15:57,090 --> 00:15:59,025
But, the other day,

277
00:15:59,426 --> 00:16:02,862
we saw the yearbook at Mr. Tabe's home,

278
00:16:03,229 --> 00:16:05,398
and there was no Kenji Rusudo
in their grade.

279
00:16:05,565 --> 00:16:06,599
Well,

280
00:16:06,766 --> 00:16:09,536
that guy had plastic surgery
to change his face,

281
00:16:09,703 --> 00:16:11,071
and changed his name too.

282
00:16:11,237 --> 00:16:12,839
What?

283
00:16:13,006 --> 00:16:14,908
His real name is Yoshio Sanpei.

284
00:16:15,375 --> 00:16:18,912
When Yoshio Sanpei drowned in
the pool, Sangenya helped him,

285
00:16:19,979 --> 00:16:21,815
and gave him mouth-to-mouth resuscitation.

286
00:16:22,882 --> 00:16:27,053
-Chief Sangenya and Mr. Rusudo kissed?
-It's mouth-to-mouth resuscitation.

287
00:16:29,155 --> 00:16:30,390
But Manager,

288
00:16:30,557 --> 00:16:33,293
don't you trust Chief Sangenya?

289
00:16:33,727 --> 00:16:37,731
Well, I trust her. I do trust her…

290
00:16:38,765 --> 00:16:40,567
Be more confident!

291
00:16:42,736 --> 00:16:43,837
Be confident?

292
00:16:44,604 --> 00:16:47,040
Right, I need to be confident, right?

293
00:16:47,907 --> 00:16:50,443
But the two of them
in that classroom during sunset…

294
00:16:53,113 --> 00:16:56,015
In that case,
I'll go see Mr. Rusudo and ask him.

295
00:16:56,483 --> 00:16:57,751
What are you going to ask him?

296
00:16:58,218 --> 00:17:00,520
I'm… I'm…

297
00:17:00,687 --> 00:17:02,956
You are going to ask him what?

298
00:17:03,556 --> 00:17:06,359
Not me!

299
00:17:06,526 --> 00:17:10,397
You should go to Chief Sangenya,
and ask her why she was with Mr. Rusudo!

300
00:17:10,563 --> 00:17:11,498
You are her husband!

301
00:17:11,664 --> 00:17:14,801
I can't do that!
Then she'll find out I was following her!

302
00:17:17,036 --> 00:17:19,973
Then, I'll have to go.

303
00:17:21,608 --> 00:17:27,414
What were you doing with Chief Sangenya
in the classroom as the sun was setting?

304
00:17:28,882 --> 00:17:31,217
Then I'll also tell him…

305
00:17:33,052 --> 00:17:37,257
"Don't go near Chief Sangenya ever again!"

306
00:17:41,728 --> 00:17:46,232
Lately, he has become quite passionate.

307
00:17:50,069 --> 00:17:53,206
Chief Sangenya kissed Mr. Rusudo?

308
00:17:53,740 --> 00:17:55,642
That's why you can't sell a house, Niwano!

309
00:17:56,075 --> 00:17:57,644
Don't act like a hotshot!

310
00:17:57,811 --> 00:17:59,179
Niwano!

311
00:18:01,147 --> 00:18:05,885
Chief Sangenya is Manager Yashiro's wife!

312
00:18:10,690 --> 00:18:11,958
What are you going to have?

313
00:18:12,492 --> 00:18:17,530
More importantly, the other day you said
that you love Chief Sangenya.

314
00:18:18,832 --> 00:18:20,700
Two "secret jewels".

315
00:18:20,867 --> 00:18:23,937
-Right away.
-Please stop harboring such love for her.

316
00:18:24,904 --> 00:18:25,972
Why?

317
00:18:26,139 --> 00:18:28,107
Why?

318
00:18:28,274 --> 00:18:30,710
Chief Sangenya
is married to Manager Yashiro.

319
00:18:30,877 --> 00:18:32,045
That's inappropriate.

320
00:18:33,446 --> 00:18:36,483
Who are you upset for, Niwano?

321
00:18:37,350 --> 00:18:39,619
For Chief Sangenya and Manager Yashiro.

322
00:18:41,721 --> 00:18:43,256
Is that really so?

323
00:18:44,891 --> 00:18:46,459
I think it's for yourself.

324
00:18:47,427 --> 00:18:48,294
Niwano…

325
00:18:49,162 --> 00:18:53,733
I think the feeling you have
for Ms. Sangenya

326
00:18:54,634 --> 00:18:55,668
is love.

327
00:18:57,504 --> 00:19:01,307
Even if it's love,

328
00:19:01,474 --> 00:19:03,776
I'm not having an affair.
An affair is not good.

329
00:19:04,310 --> 00:19:08,948
I told you that I have feelings
for Ms. Sangenya,

330
00:19:10,316 --> 00:19:13,920
but I never asked her to love me
in return.

331
00:19:14,420 --> 00:19:17,323
I have no intention of breaking up
her family either.

332
00:19:17,490 --> 00:19:19,325
But you two met alone.

333
00:19:19,826 --> 00:19:23,663
What? How do you know that, Niwano?

334
00:19:26,799 --> 00:19:28,902
Well, let's leave that aside.

335
00:19:29,769 --> 00:19:33,606
I was asked by Ms. Sangenya
to meet with her.

336
00:19:35,975 --> 00:19:37,176
Thank you for waiting.

337
00:19:39,913 --> 00:19:46,753
Niwano, the feeling you and I have
for Ms. Sangenya is the same.

338
00:19:47,720 --> 00:19:49,956
I'm not having an affair.

339
00:19:51,090 --> 00:19:55,094
Just thinking of her quietly
is not an affair.

340
00:19:55,795 --> 00:19:58,197
The freedom of the heart

341
00:19:58,898 --> 00:20:04,504
to be in love with someone secretly,
is the right every human possesses.

342
00:20:06,839 --> 00:20:09,943
I think it's unforgivable when someone
intrudes into

343
00:20:10,777 --> 00:20:16,082
the hidden feelings of another
that are buried deep in their hearts.

344
00:20:19,319 --> 00:20:22,622
Freedom of secretly
being in love with someone.

345
00:20:23,189 --> 00:20:26,459
Right, we are the same.

346
00:20:29,495 --> 00:20:33,600
Here's to the freedom of secretly
being in love with someone. Cheers.

347
00:20:33,766 --> 00:20:34,901
Cheers.

348
00:20:37,704 --> 00:20:38,838
Winner, Fujii!

349
00:20:42,909 --> 00:20:45,178
That was close, Ninomiya.

350
00:20:46,312 --> 00:20:49,282
-Oh hey.
-Mr. Rusudo is not here yet?

351
00:20:49,449 --> 00:20:50,883
No, he's not here yet.

352
00:20:52,118 --> 00:20:53,052
Thank you.

353
00:20:54,587 --> 00:20:57,190
Here we go! Cheese!

354
00:21:00,860 --> 00:21:03,630
I'm going to send this to Mr. Adachi.

355
00:21:03,796 --> 00:21:10,336
Let's see.
"I'm having a drink with Mr. Rusudo.

356
00:21:10,737 --> 00:21:13,172
Why don't you come join us, Mr. Adachi?"

357
00:21:13,473 --> 00:21:15,074
Okay, send.

358
00:21:17,176 --> 00:21:18,378
Winner, Adachi!

359
00:21:22,649 --> 00:21:23,916
He didn't come.

360
00:21:25,151 --> 00:21:26,119
Here you go.

361
00:21:26,619 --> 00:21:30,323
Lately, Mr. Rusudo's been here
during the daytime.

362
00:21:30,490 --> 00:21:33,626
-What?
-No way…

363
00:21:33,793 --> 00:21:38,231
It's as if our space is slowly
being invaded by him.

364
00:21:38,398 --> 00:21:41,234
Well, I can't tell him not to come though.

365
00:21:41,401 --> 00:21:42,335
Right.

366
00:21:42,502 --> 00:21:43,803
You are right about that.

367
00:21:45,471 --> 00:21:48,808
That story about
the two extramarital affairs was fun.

368
00:21:48,975 --> 00:21:50,610
You found it fun?

369
00:21:50,777 --> 00:21:54,313
What do you mean? You were clearly
going against Sangenya today.

370
00:21:54,480 --> 00:21:58,718
Well, I wasn't going against her. I just
don't understand how she can accept that.

371
00:21:59,118 --> 00:22:01,688
Of course I think it's better
if we can sell houses,

372
00:22:02,021 --> 00:22:04,290
and it's an ironclad rule for realtors

373
00:22:04,457 --> 00:22:06,292
not to meddle
with clients' private matters.

374
00:22:06,926 --> 00:22:09,262
We basically think the same way.

375
00:22:09,429 --> 00:22:13,166
Being married sounds complicated.
I'm glad I didn't get married.

376
00:22:13,332 --> 00:22:17,870
That's right! It's impossible
to just focus on each other forever.

377
00:22:18,337 --> 00:22:24,477
Ah, but lately, my wife is really
into Korean drama,

378
00:22:24,644 --> 00:22:27,113
and she seems so much more
beautiful than before.

379
00:22:27,280 --> 00:22:29,749
I wonder if that's the work
of her hormones.

380
00:22:29,916 --> 00:22:33,786
She's into a Korean drama star
that's all the way across the sea?

381
00:22:34,387 --> 00:22:38,324
Maybe it's good to have something
you can be focused on.

382
00:22:38,491 --> 00:22:39,358
What?

383
00:22:39,726 --> 00:22:44,230
So just like that customer today
who has extramarital affairs,

384
00:22:44,630 --> 00:22:48,901
maybe it's possible for a married couple
to be happy with an open marriage.

385
00:22:49,302 --> 00:22:51,237
What? You said, "moral crisis"!

386
00:22:51,804 --> 00:22:55,108
Well, that's that, this is this.
There's logic to both sides.

387
00:22:55,675 --> 00:22:58,444
That's Fuse for you! You are so cool!

388
00:22:58,611 --> 00:23:01,247
After all, you used to be really popular!

389
00:23:01,414 --> 00:23:03,316
No, no.

390
00:23:08,955 --> 00:23:10,523
Please be assured…

391
00:23:10,757 --> 00:23:14,427
Chief Sangenya and Rusudo
are not having an affair.

392
00:23:14,594 --> 00:23:16,195
There is no way!

393
00:23:16,362 --> 00:23:17,663
That was the report.

394
00:23:18,965 --> 00:23:21,934
-What? Is it Sangenya?
-No, that's not it.

395
00:23:24,704 --> 00:23:29,876
So Chief Sangenya's line is, "That's
why you can't sell a house, Niwano!"

396
00:23:30,042 --> 00:23:32,178
She says it at least once a day.

397
00:23:32,945 --> 00:23:35,348
Niwano, are you that bad
at selling houses?

398
00:23:35,515 --> 00:23:39,786
Of course! Compared to
Chief Sangenya, no one is good at it.

399
00:23:40,753 --> 00:23:44,457
But when I'm down
due to my lack of ability,

400
00:23:44,924 --> 00:23:47,660
then she yells at me,
"Don't act like a hotshot!"

401
00:23:48,995 --> 00:23:49,862
You seem happy.

402
00:23:50,730 --> 00:23:52,732
Well, I'm scared but happy.

403
00:23:54,200 --> 00:23:58,371
Are you in charge of the same client
as Ms. Sangenya right now?

404
00:23:58,538 --> 00:24:01,440
Yes, after all, I am Sangenya Children.

405
00:24:02,041 --> 00:24:03,142
What's your client like?

406
00:24:04,310 --> 00:24:08,281
Well, it's a married couple
and they're both having an affair.

407
00:24:08,681 --> 00:24:11,984
They do get along, but they have
separate bedrooms,

408
00:24:12,451 --> 00:24:14,554
and they believe
that by seeing other people,

409
00:24:14,720 --> 00:24:18,291
they'd get along better. They are strange.

410
00:24:18,558 --> 00:24:20,359
-I see.
-Yes.

411
00:24:20,526 --> 00:24:21,460
Kenji.

412
00:24:22,461 --> 00:24:24,664
-Oh!
-So this is where you were.

413
00:24:26,999 --> 00:24:28,835
What are you seeing Kenji for, Niwano?

414
00:24:29,802 --> 00:24:32,305
Kenji?

415
00:24:32,471 --> 00:24:35,408
I'm sorry I didn't go fencing, Satoshi.

416
00:24:37,443 --> 00:24:39,111
What were you two talking about?

417
00:24:39,579 --> 00:24:42,748
About that affair thing we were all
talking about today.

418
00:24:42,915 --> 00:24:45,918
I wasn't in the office all day today.

419
00:24:46,085 --> 00:24:48,120
Oh, so you weren't there then.

420
00:24:48,287 --> 00:24:52,692
And the husband's girlfriend

421
00:24:52,859 --> 00:24:57,163
is married too, and her name is Oda Mari!

422
00:24:58,297 --> 00:25:01,434
Your wife's name is Mari?

423
00:25:01,601 --> 00:25:02,635
Oda Mari!

424
00:25:03,669 --> 00:25:06,639
She's the kind who makes you shut up.

425
00:25:06,806 --> 00:25:08,741
Even her name is a pun of "shut up".

426
00:25:08,908 --> 00:25:12,378
I shouldn't laugh, but I can't help it.

427
00:25:13,412 --> 00:25:15,181
Don't get so excited!

428
00:25:49,315 --> 00:25:53,519
Manager! Manager! Over here!

429
00:25:53,686 --> 00:25:55,688
Over here!

430
00:25:56,322 --> 00:25:58,658
You seem lonely again today.

431
00:25:58,824 --> 00:26:00,693
Go on with your work.

432
00:26:00,860 --> 00:26:03,195
You are shopping alone?

433
00:26:03,362 --> 00:26:04,830
Leave me alone.

434
00:26:04,997 --> 00:26:08,267
My Sangenya is a super realtor,

435
00:26:08,434 --> 00:26:12,204
but when she's home, she is a super wife
who does all the housework.

436
00:26:14,006 --> 00:26:20,112
It's terminal when you defend
your marriage outside of the home.

437
00:26:20,846 --> 00:26:21,914
Good evening.

438
00:26:23,049 --> 00:26:24,650
How is your cold?

439
00:26:24,817 --> 00:26:28,955
Oh, thank you. I feel better with
that ginger Kudzu drink.

440
00:26:29,121 --> 00:26:31,524
Oh, I'm glad.

441
00:26:32,458 --> 00:26:34,226
Ah, Manager!

442
00:26:34,493 --> 00:26:36,896
How about this new product
of mustard stewed mackerel?

443
00:26:37,063 --> 00:26:39,598
Don't take that one! That's dangerous.

444
00:26:50,943 --> 00:26:52,378
Thanks for waiting.

445
00:26:52,545 --> 00:26:53,479
Hi.

446
00:26:53,646 --> 00:26:57,650
-You must be cold.
-I'm fine. Let's go.

447
00:27:04,123 --> 00:27:06,292
I'll call you again, okay?

448
00:27:06,459 --> 00:27:07,727
When?

449
00:27:07,960 --> 00:27:09,328
Either tonight, or tomorrow?

450
00:27:09,495 --> 00:27:10,963
Ok, I'll be waiting.

451
00:27:11,130 --> 00:27:12,231
See you!

452
00:27:12,398 --> 00:27:15,401
TEIKO REAL ESTATE

453
00:27:21,440 --> 00:27:22,975
A realtor?

454
00:27:25,044 --> 00:27:28,447
Thank you for coming in today.

455
00:27:29,015 --> 00:27:31,484
We can finally have our own house.

456
00:27:31,650 --> 00:27:33,019
It's a house with great Feng Shui.

457
00:27:33,452 --> 00:27:36,489
Ms. Sangenya, thank you for finding
such a perfect place.

458
00:27:37,123 --> 00:27:39,759
This is the official contract.

459
00:27:40,292 --> 00:27:44,163
We will explain this disclosure statement

460
00:27:44,463 --> 00:27:46,432
in compliance with the real estate
law article 35.

461
00:27:46,599 --> 00:27:49,268
Please let us know
if you have any questions.

462
00:27:49,668 --> 00:27:52,505
Once you agree, we will move on
to signing these documents.

463
00:27:53,439 --> 00:27:55,241
-Niwano.
-Yes.

464
00:27:55,908 --> 00:27:57,777
I will start now.

465
00:27:58,344 --> 00:28:02,081
-I will start--
-I won't allow you to buy that house!

466
00:28:03,816 --> 00:28:05,551
-Who is he?
-I'm not sure.

467
00:28:05,718 --> 00:28:10,222
Do you understand how sinful
your conduct is?

468
00:28:10,389 --> 00:28:13,726
Please wait. Who are you?

469
00:28:14,326 --> 00:28:15,428
I'm Junpei Oda!

470
00:28:15,995 --> 00:28:20,566
I'm Junpei Oda, the husband
of your girlfriend, Mari Oda!

471
00:28:21,200 --> 00:28:22,768
Mari Oda? Oh!

472
00:28:23,402 --> 00:28:27,873
You intend to buy a house for Mari,
and marry her?

473
00:28:28,374 --> 00:28:30,242
I won't divorce her.

474
00:28:30,643 --> 00:28:31,610
Mr. Oda.

475
00:28:32,912 --> 00:28:35,714
The home Minato Yasoda is going
to purchase now

476
00:28:35,881 --> 00:28:40,419
is for him and his wife and it's not
for your wife.

477
00:28:41,620 --> 00:28:45,591
Then are you lying to Mari
and toying with her?

478
00:28:46,058 --> 00:28:48,561
Isn't this considered
a trespass or something?

479
00:28:48,727 --> 00:28:52,298
Hey you, Yasoda! Answer my question!

480
00:28:52,465 --> 00:28:53,666
Huh? What question?

481
00:28:54,266 --> 00:28:57,736
He asked whether you are toying
with Ms. Mari.

482
00:28:57,903 --> 00:28:59,738
I'm not doing that.

483
00:28:59,905 --> 00:29:04,410
We started dating knowing the fact
that we are both married.

484
00:29:05,277 --> 00:29:06,445
What is this?

485
00:29:06,812 --> 00:29:09,882
I have no intention of breaking
your marriage,

486
00:29:10,049 --> 00:29:13,385
and my wife accepts
the fact that I'm dating Mari.

487
00:29:13,853 --> 00:29:17,690
In our marriage, we agreed
to have an open relationship.

488
00:29:17,857 --> 00:29:19,592
We get along better that way.

489
00:29:19,758 --> 00:29:22,695
What are you saying?
I don't get it at all.

490
00:29:22,862 --> 00:29:25,898
Maybe some people won't get it,
but that's how it is.

491
00:29:26,065 --> 00:29:29,235
So I'm buying a house with my wife,
and it doesn't concern your wife.

492
00:29:29,768 --> 00:29:30,803
People like you…

493
00:29:31,403 --> 00:29:33,005
corrupt this world.

494
00:29:34,206 --> 00:29:37,243
My precious Mari… It's unforgivable!

495
00:29:37,409 --> 00:29:39,879
Please be quiet!

496
00:29:41,413 --> 00:29:45,918
Stop telling me to be quiet.

497
00:30:13,979 --> 00:30:14,980
What was that?

498
00:30:15,648 --> 00:30:16,582
Maybe a terrorist attack?

499
00:30:16,749 --> 00:30:17,850
Terrorist attack?

500
00:30:24,657 --> 00:30:27,092
Why did you say such a thing?

501
00:30:27,259 --> 00:30:30,329
I thought he needed
to let it all out once to calm down.

502
00:30:30,496 --> 00:30:31,764
For what?

503
00:30:32,431 --> 00:30:34,066
To sell a house.

504
00:30:34,233 --> 00:30:35,568
Are you okay?

505
00:30:38,137 --> 00:30:40,372
-Ouch!
-No, it doesn't.

506
00:30:40,539 --> 00:30:43,709
Shouldn't this be done by Tokoshima?

507
00:30:43,876 --> 00:30:46,345
I'm an office worker and not a nurse.

508
00:30:46,512 --> 00:30:47,780
I'm not a nurse either.

509
00:30:47,947 --> 00:30:50,015
You were a nurse the other day though.

510
00:30:50,249 --> 00:30:54,520
Who'd have thought
the bronze Sumo-kun statue made for

511
00:30:54,687 --> 00:30:57,823
Teko Real Estate's 30th anniversary
would harm someone.

512
00:30:57,990 --> 00:30:58,924
I'm sorry.

513
00:30:59,091 --> 00:31:00,626
It's not your fault, Niwano.

514
00:31:00,793 --> 00:31:02,595
It's all because of an affair.

515
00:31:02,761 --> 00:31:04,096
That's right.

516
00:31:04,263 --> 00:31:08,167
Why don't they just love their wives?

517
00:31:08,334 --> 00:31:11,203
The person who hit Niwano
is a college professor,

518
00:31:11,370 --> 00:31:13,472
who married his student, right?

519
00:31:13,872 --> 00:31:17,676
He's also a dirty old man who likes
younger women.

520
00:31:17,843 --> 00:31:19,612
I don't think you should label
people like that!

521
00:31:21,313 --> 00:31:23,015
True love isn't limited

522
00:31:23,449 --> 00:31:25,618
to relationships that are
considered the norm.

523
00:31:26,252 --> 00:31:27,586
What do you mean, Adachi?

524
00:31:28,754 --> 00:31:31,457
Nothing. I was just mumbling to myself.

525
00:31:31,890 --> 00:31:33,659
That was some intense mumbling.

526
00:31:34,226 --> 00:31:37,296
I just hope you're not entangled
in a messy relationship.

527
00:31:37,463 --> 00:31:41,233
I hope it's not an affair.
An affair is a no-no.

528
00:31:41,400 --> 00:31:42,501
Really?

529
00:31:42,968 --> 00:31:47,373
Maybe an affair is a "yes"
that's close to a "no"?

530
00:31:48,040 --> 00:31:50,309
A "yes" close to a "no"?

531
00:31:50,476 --> 00:31:51,410
What do you mean?

532
00:31:51,877 --> 00:31:57,216
It's better not to have an affair,
but it can't be helped either.

533
00:31:58,384 --> 00:32:00,386
I'd say it's a blurred line.

534
00:32:00,552 --> 00:32:02,454
Blurred line?

535
00:32:03,889 --> 00:32:08,193
I knew that Mari was married.

536
00:32:09,361 --> 00:32:12,898
I assumed that they were like
my wife and me,

537
00:32:13,065 --> 00:32:16,168
and that her husband accepted
her relationship with me.

538
00:32:16,335 --> 00:32:22,608
I don't think there are many
couples that really agree to that.

539
00:32:23,242 --> 00:32:25,377
I didn't realize her husband
was that much older,

540
00:32:25,944 --> 00:32:30,649
and that he'd be so jealous. I'm in shock.

541
00:32:31,917 --> 00:32:35,087
Well, I'm glad you didn't get hurt.

542
00:32:35,254 --> 00:32:38,857
I'm sorry that Mr. Niwano got hurt
because of me.

543
00:32:39,258 --> 00:32:43,829
Oh no. It's our job to protect
our client's safety.

544
00:32:46,565 --> 00:32:49,635
I thought our way of life was fine,

545
00:32:49,802 --> 00:32:52,004
but now…

546
00:32:53,706 --> 00:32:55,908
I'm not so sure anymore.

547
00:32:56,075 --> 00:33:00,479
I might have to reconsider my relationship

548
00:33:01,280 --> 00:33:03,349
with my wife and with Mari.

549
00:33:06,985 --> 00:33:11,490
Ms. Sangenya, regarding the house we
were going to sign today…

550
00:33:12,424 --> 00:33:16,362
I would like to put it on hold for now.

551
00:33:16,528 --> 00:33:17,763
-I understand.
-What?

552
00:33:17,930 --> 00:33:19,732
That's a bit…

553
00:33:19,898 --> 00:33:20,966
I'm sorry.

554
00:33:22,067 --> 00:33:23,535
Minato! Are you okay?

555
00:33:23,702 --> 00:33:25,237
I'm fine.

556
00:33:25,404 --> 00:33:28,006
When I called Mr. Niwano,
he said something happened,

557
00:33:28,173 --> 00:33:29,742
so I came as soon as possible.

558
00:33:29,908 --> 00:33:33,112
I'm sorry that Niwano mentioned
something you didn't need to know.

559
00:33:33,278 --> 00:33:36,615
We will put your purchase on hold for now.

560
00:33:36,782 --> 00:33:38,884
Thank you for coming today.

561
00:33:40,252 --> 00:33:41,253
What's going on?

562
00:33:46,325 --> 00:33:48,494
Thank you very much.

563
00:33:52,231 --> 00:33:54,700
That's rare for you to let go
of your clients like that.

564
00:33:54,867 --> 00:33:57,136
-I didn't let them go.
-But you just--

565
00:33:57,302 --> 00:34:00,539
I will sell a house
to Mr. and Mrs. Yasoda for sure!

566
00:34:02,141 --> 00:34:04,743
There is no house I can't sell.

567
00:34:11,183 --> 00:34:15,154
I felt like I'd end up hitting Mari
if I stayed with her today.

568
00:34:16,255 --> 00:34:18,190
So I sent her back to her
mother's tonight.

569
00:34:20,025 --> 00:34:24,163
I think she will think things
through there.

570
00:34:24,596 --> 00:34:25,864
I'm sure.

571
00:34:28,901 --> 00:34:30,002
Mr. Rusudo…

572
00:34:30,736 --> 00:34:36,508
Isn't marriage about vowing
your eternal love to your partner?

573
00:34:37,409 --> 00:34:38,510
Yes, it is.

574
00:34:39,311 --> 00:34:42,047
Maybe you won't get it since
you are single…

575
00:34:42,448 --> 00:34:43,882
I don't get it either.

576
00:34:45,184 --> 00:34:49,421
I've only loved one person
in my life so far.

577
00:34:50,422 --> 00:34:52,891
You can't be with that person?

578
00:34:53,058 --> 00:34:54,059
You can't be with her?

579
00:34:55,194 --> 00:35:00,165
That's why I won't ever
get married to anyone.

580
00:35:00,699 --> 00:35:02,434
That's sad.

581
00:35:02,601 --> 00:35:05,404
-That's so depressing.
-Do you mind…

582
00:35:05,938 --> 00:35:07,873
-Kokoro?
-Yes.

583
00:35:09,741 --> 00:35:11,877
But that's what love is.

584
00:35:13,579 --> 00:35:16,682
If married couples take on lovers,
and they each

585
00:35:16,849 --> 00:35:20,786
accept that kind of a relationship,
that's a sham. It's disgusting.

586
00:35:21,753 --> 00:35:23,522
I'm just like you, Mr. Rusudo.

587
00:35:24,456 --> 00:35:28,861
I will never be in love with anyone else
besides Mari.

588
00:35:29,795 --> 00:35:30,929
That's for sure.

589
00:35:47,813 --> 00:35:48,881
Mr. Rusudo…

590
00:35:54,653 --> 00:35:59,024
You all must be uneasy because
of what happened yesterday.

591
00:35:59,424 --> 00:36:04,530
However, don't forget the fact
that the home is the base

592
00:36:04,696 --> 00:36:07,432
of people's happiness. That means--

593
00:36:07,599 --> 00:36:09,768
Manager! It's too long.

594
00:36:10,469 --> 00:36:12,337
Oh, is that so?

595
00:36:12,938 --> 00:36:16,542
Well then, go ahead and tell us
your schedule for today?

596
00:36:17,042 --> 00:36:19,978
Today, we'll carry out
an important mission

597
00:36:20,145 --> 00:36:22,381
to sell a house to Mr. and Mrs. Yasoda.

598
00:36:23,282 --> 00:36:24,283
A mission?

599
00:36:24,650 --> 00:36:28,587
For that, I've called in a powerful
business partner.

600
00:36:28,987 --> 00:36:30,355
Please come in.

601
00:36:38,931 --> 00:36:39,998
Kenji.

602
00:36:40,866 --> 00:36:41,733
Morning.

603
00:36:43,302 --> 00:36:44,536
Cute.

604
00:36:45,304 --> 00:36:46,805
I'm Kenji Rusudo.

605
00:36:47,272 --> 00:36:51,677
Everyone, let's all work together
to sell a house today.

606
00:36:52,644 --> 00:36:53,645
What's going on?

607
00:36:54,079 --> 00:36:56,682
Sangenya, I didn't know anything
about this.

608
00:36:57,449 --> 00:36:59,117
It's to sell a house.

609
00:37:01,219 --> 00:37:04,890
Now, we will create a fateful encounter.

610
00:37:06,258 --> 00:37:09,928
I call it, "Make Destiny Operation"!

611
00:37:10,796 --> 00:37:11,663
That's wonderful.

612
00:37:14,166 --> 00:37:15,667
It makes no sense at all.

613
00:37:15,834 --> 00:37:17,035
Gather around!

614
00:37:17,736 --> 00:37:18,570
Yes.

615
00:37:27,646 --> 00:37:29,114
Mr. Junpei Oda passed the intersection.

616
00:37:29,281 --> 00:37:30,649
One minute to the scene.

617
00:37:30,849 --> 00:37:33,151
I got it. Thank you, Satoshi.

618
00:37:38,690 --> 00:37:40,425
I'm at the top of the slope.

619
00:37:41,526 --> 00:37:42,928
Mr. Junpei Oda is coming.

620
00:37:50,102 --> 00:37:51,336
He's at the bottom of the slope.

621
00:37:51,503 --> 00:37:54,940
Three seconds to go, two, one…

622
00:37:56,274 --> 00:37:58,276
-Mr. Oda!
-Oh!

623
00:38:01,980 --> 00:38:04,583
Ms. Tsugumi Yasoda is almost
at the top of the slope.

624
00:38:04,750 --> 00:38:06,918
Operation Orange , start!

625
00:38:07,085 --> 00:38:07,953
Roger.

626
00:38:18,330 --> 00:38:19,498
Oh no!

627
00:38:31,309 --> 00:38:32,911
Thank you. You are so kind.

628
00:38:33,078 --> 00:38:35,681
Not at all. Are you okay?

629
00:38:40,352 --> 00:38:41,319
Yes.

630
00:38:45,924 --> 00:38:46,892
Go.

631
00:38:52,664 --> 00:38:55,300
Ms. Tsugumi Yasoda is about to pass by.

632
00:38:56,568 --> 00:38:57,469
I got it.

633
00:38:59,504 --> 00:39:00,706
Hey, what's up?

634
00:39:00,872 --> 00:39:03,508
Mr. Junpei Oda is about to pass by.

635
00:39:04,342 --> 00:39:05,477
Got it.

636
00:39:15,420 --> 00:39:18,023
Don't look at me like that.

637
00:39:18,890 --> 00:39:22,194
Huh? You were looking at me
just now, right?

638
00:39:23,228 --> 00:39:24,730
Wait, wait.

639
00:39:26,598 --> 00:39:28,900
Leave her alone!

640
00:39:29,267 --> 00:39:31,436
What? Where are you from?

641
00:39:34,372 --> 00:39:36,508
I'm a fifth-level black belt in judo.

642
00:39:36,675 --> 00:39:39,244
I'm sorry. Let me go. Let me go.

643
00:39:41,680 --> 00:39:42,881
I'll get you one day!

644
00:39:44,282 --> 00:39:45,584
Thank you very much.

645
00:39:46,752 --> 00:39:49,354
Oh! I saw you the other day!

646
00:39:50,689 --> 00:39:52,691
So there are coincidences like this?

647
00:39:58,063 --> 00:39:59,164
Go, go.

648
00:40:02,100 --> 00:40:04,236
Thank you very much.

649
00:40:09,274 --> 00:40:10,242
Go, go, go.

650
00:40:17,749 --> 00:40:18,850
Thank you.

651
00:40:26,858 --> 00:40:28,960
The mission was a success.

652
00:40:29,127 --> 00:40:30,829
GREAT!

653
00:40:38,036 --> 00:40:41,139
It's not that I've come to hate my wife.

654
00:40:42,040 --> 00:40:45,010
But my mind is filled
with thoughts about you.

655
00:40:45,177 --> 00:40:46,278
Me too.

656
00:40:47,312 --> 00:40:50,916
I always used to say
that affairs are unforgivable,

657
00:40:51,116 --> 00:40:53,585
but here I am.

658
00:40:54,085 --> 00:40:57,656
My husband is my precious
business partner.

659
00:40:58,456 --> 00:41:01,026
I respect him and his skills too.

660
00:41:01,193 --> 00:41:02,160
But

661
00:41:02,894 --> 00:41:05,230
I like you, Mr. Oda.

662
00:41:06,264 --> 00:41:08,733
We've gotten crazy, huh?

663
00:41:09,501 --> 00:41:11,670
Would you like to buy a house?

664
00:41:12,337 --> 00:41:13,505
Who are you?

665
00:41:14,539 --> 00:41:15,607
Ms. Sangenya.

666
00:41:16,274 --> 00:41:17,909
She's a realtor in Shinjuku.

667
00:41:19,678 --> 00:41:21,780
I'm sorry about the other day .

668
00:41:23,815 --> 00:41:26,351
We're not in a situation right now
where we can buy a house.

669
00:41:26,518 --> 00:41:28,420
You are both having an affair, correct?

670
00:41:28,854 --> 00:41:29,821
I make no excuses.

671
00:41:31,056 --> 00:41:32,290
I know it's ridiculous.

672
00:41:33,225 --> 00:41:35,227
Would you like to buy a house?

673
00:41:35,393 --> 00:41:38,296
So like we just said,
now is not the time for that.

674
00:41:38,463 --> 00:41:42,634
The place I want to recommend,
is not a house for the two of you.

675
00:41:43,268 --> 00:41:45,203
TEIKO REAL ESTATE

676
00:41:45,837 --> 00:41:46,938
Here.

677
00:41:47,973 --> 00:41:48,907
Please enjoy.

678
00:41:50,342 --> 00:41:53,645
Tokoshima, put that away.

679
00:41:59,918 --> 00:42:02,621
I had you all come here today…

680
00:42:03,788 --> 00:42:04,656
Go ahead.

681
00:42:11,029 --> 00:42:15,533
It's to have Mr. and Mrs. Yasoda and
Mr. and Mrs. Oda buy a house.

682
00:42:15,700 --> 00:42:17,135
You are quite persistent.

683
00:42:17,569 --> 00:42:19,838
We are not in
that kind of a situation right now.

684
00:42:20,005 --> 00:42:21,940
Right.

685
00:42:22,107 --> 00:42:24,509
It's so strange when the four of us
are here together.

686
00:42:24,676 --> 00:42:26,344
I understand it's strange.

687
00:42:26,511 --> 00:42:29,881
Now I'm going to resolve
this strange situation.

688
00:42:30,815 --> 00:42:34,319
Mr. Minato Yasoda and Mrs. Tsugumi
are married.

689
00:42:34,486 --> 00:42:37,756
Mr. Junpei Oda and Mrs. Mari
are married too.

690
00:42:38,256 --> 00:42:41,693
Mr. Minato and Mrs. Mari are in love,

691
00:42:41,860 --> 00:42:45,830
and Mrs. Tsugumi and Mr. Junpei
are in love as well.

692
00:42:45,997 --> 00:42:49,968
If this is the case,
isn't it better for everyone

693
00:42:50,135 --> 00:42:54,239
to get a divorce first, then remarry?

694
00:42:54,406 --> 00:42:55,373
That's not it.

695
00:42:55,874 --> 00:42:56,808
Why?

696
00:42:57,275 --> 00:43:00,979
These couples need both the "eros" type
of love between a man and a woman

697
00:43:01,146 --> 00:43:04,282
and love that goes beyond anything sexual.

698
00:43:06,351 --> 00:43:12,257
According to this chart,
this relationship is "home",

699
00:43:13,358 --> 00:43:17,295
and this relationship is "eros".

700
00:43:18,096 --> 00:43:19,898
Home and eros.

701
00:43:20,265 --> 00:43:22,834
-Home and…
-Eros.

702
00:43:23,268 --> 00:43:25,804
-Home and…
-Eros!

703
00:43:25,971 --> 00:43:29,774
That's right. "Home" and "eros".

704
00:43:29,941 --> 00:43:32,143
A human's heart is balanced
with both types of love.

705
00:43:33,511 --> 00:43:37,115
Most people try to possess
both types of love,

706
00:43:37,282 --> 00:43:39,784
but end up giving up on one or the other.

707
00:43:39,951 --> 00:43:44,956
But these couples have a strong desire
to possess both types of love.

708
00:43:45,623 --> 00:43:47,959
Having such strong desires means…

709
00:43:48,393 --> 00:43:50,528
What does it mean?

710
00:43:50,929 --> 00:43:53,932
That there is power burning inside of you.

711
00:43:54,099 --> 00:43:56,301
It's proof that you are alive.

712
00:43:57,135 --> 00:44:00,705
Society will brand
these relationships as an "affair".

713
00:44:01,039 --> 00:44:03,608
But the feeling of loving someone

714
00:44:03,775 --> 00:44:07,345
is the source of fire
that keeps life burning bright!

715
00:44:09,114 --> 00:44:13,752
That may be true,
but it's all so absurd and unreasonable…

716
00:44:13,918 --> 00:44:19,758
Even so, if the parties involved are happy
with the situation, then it's all right.

717
00:44:20,492 --> 00:44:23,161
What others think of you,
should mean nothing to you.

718
00:44:23,328 --> 00:44:24,996
There it is! "Nothing"!

719
00:44:25,430 --> 00:44:30,368
The Yasoda couple and the Oda couple,
should keep a stable quadrilateral,

720
00:44:30,535 --> 00:44:33,805
balancing your relationships with both
the "home" and "eros" of love.

721
00:44:34,439 --> 00:44:36,274
A stable quadrilateral.

722
00:44:36,441 --> 00:44:39,477
But does that mean
things will remain the same as before?

723
00:44:39,644 --> 00:44:42,480
But I don't know if we should remain
the same as before.

724
00:44:42,914 --> 00:44:46,051
You think so. I think there's "nothing"
to worry about.

725
00:44:46,618 --> 00:44:47,619
I agree.

726
00:44:47,786 --> 00:44:49,287
No one asked for your opinion, Niwano!

727
00:44:49,454 --> 00:44:50,321
Yes.

728
00:44:50,488 --> 00:44:53,091
To Mr. Minato and Mrs. Tsugumi Yasoda,

729
00:44:53,258 --> 00:44:57,929
I will once again suggest that apartment
with perfect Feng Shui.

730
00:44:58,096 --> 00:45:00,765
For Mr. Junpei Oda and Mrs. Mari,

731
00:45:00,932 --> 00:45:05,403
I will suggest another unit in
the same complex.

732
00:45:05,737 --> 00:45:10,642
Living far away makes it hard to switch
between "home" and "eros".

733
00:45:10,809 --> 00:45:14,245
Which means you will be wasting time
while traveling to meet up together.

734
00:45:14,612 --> 00:45:15,980
But…

735
00:45:16,147 --> 00:45:18,683
If you all live in the same
apartment complex,

736
00:45:18,850 --> 00:45:22,654
you will not waste time
while switching from "home" to "eros".

737
00:45:23,388 --> 00:45:25,356
I see.

738
00:45:25,523 --> 00:45:29,994
While maintaining the connection
and memories between the married couples…

739
00:45:30,495 --> 00:45:33,631
You can still freely enjoy
your current romantic relationship.

740
00:45:34,399 --> 00:45:36,134
That is what we suggest.

741
00:45:36,534 --> 00:45:37,502
They harmonized.

742
00:45:38,803 --> 00:45:41,573
Shall we go take a look at
that house again?

743
00:45:43,341 --> 00:45:46,678
Shall we move to the same complex?

744
00:45:48,813 --> 00:45:50,081
I've got them.

745
00:45:50,882 --> 00:45:52,050
We got them.

746
00:45:54,819 --> 00:45:58,123
-Thank you very much.
-Thank you.

747
00:46:00,725 --> 00:46:03,862
I sold the house with perfect Feng Shui
to Mr. and Mrs. Yasoda.

748
00:46:04,429 --> 00:46:05,530
Good job.

749
00:46:06,064 --> 00:46:09,267
Thank you for your cooperation.

750
00:46:10,001 --> 00:46:13,838
I sold a unit in the same complex
to Mr. and Mrs. Oda.

751
00:46:14,239 --> 00:46:17,308
I see. You came all the way to say that?

752
00:46:18,776 --> 00:46:19,711
Ms. Sangenya.

753
00:46:21,579 --> 00:46:24,048
I had fun. Thank you.

754
00:46:24,782 --> 00:46:27,886
Thank you for your help.

755
00:46:38,930 --> 00:46:40,732
See you.

756
00:46:42,367 --> 00:46:46,204
Oh, the exit is over there.

757
00:46:48,573 --> 00:46:49,807
Thank you.

758
00:47:00,919 --> 00:47:04,022
I'm going to look at the third location
in Daikanyama.

759
00:47:04,622 --> 00:47:08,059
Business really improved
after moving here.

760
00:47:08,226 --> 00:47:09,794
Amazing Feng Shui.

761
00:47:09,961 --> 00:47:12,764
Should we change all the mirrors
at the shop to octagon shapes?

762
00:47:13,231 --> 00:47:14,866
No, it'll be too expensive.

763
00:47:15,033 --> 00:47:17,035
What? That'll be nothing.

764
00:47:17,202 --> 00:47:18,136
No.

765
00:47:19,704 --> 00:47:21,039
You've got some on your face.

766
00:47:22,273 --> 00:47:23,908
-There?
-Here?

767
00:47:25,176 --> 00:47:26,978
I'll mix your natto for you.

768
00:47:28,046 --> 00:47:31,449
I'll go senile
if you continue to treat me like a kid.

769
00:47:32,150 --> 00:47:35,587
It'll be okay,
as long as you have a lover.

770
00:47:36,921 --> 00:47:38,089
I guess so.

771
00:47:40,992 --> 00:47:42,093
-Thanks for waiting.
-Hey.

772
00:47:45,964 --> 00:47:47,265
-Where should we go?
-Hm?

773
00:47:47,432 --> 00:47:49,701
-Where should we go?
-Let's see…

774
00:47:50,668 --> 00:47:52,303
-Want to eat something?
-Pizza.

775
00:47:52,470 --> 00:47:53,371
-Pizza?
-Yeah.

776
00:47:57,875 --> 00:47:58,810
Sangenya.

777
00:47:58,977 --> 00:47:59,978
Yes.

778
00:48:01,479 --> 00:48:05,917
Do you accept extramarital affairs?

779
00:48:10,188 --> 00:48:11,956
I don't like it.

780
00:48:12,857 --> 00:48:15,026
I don't want a stable quadrilateral.

781
00:48:16,427 --> 00:48:18,696
It's all to sell a house.

782
00:48:20,698 --> 00:48:22,934
I have an appointment now, so I'm off.

783
00:48:23,201 --> 00:48:26,471
Your dinner is in the fridge
labelled "tonight's dinner",

784
00:48:26,638 --> 00:48:29,641
so please microwave it and eat it.
See you.

785
00:48:39,550 --> 00:48:42,387
Mackerel rich in DHA!

786
00:48:42,553 --> 00:48:45,523
If you want to live forever,
let's eat some mackerel!

787
00:48:45,690 --> 00:48:48,092
It goes well with wine… oh?

788
00:48:48,393 --> 00:48:49,961
Manager!

789
00:48:50,895 --> 00:48:55,199
You look pathetic as usual!

790
00:48:55,700 --> 00:48:56,934
Good evening.

791
00:48:57,669 --> 00:48:58,636
Oh…

792
00:48:58,803 --> 00:49:00,738
You seem tired tonight again.

793
00:49:01,506 --> 00:49:02,707
Well…

794
00:49:03,341 --> 00:49:04,609
I'm worried.

795
00:49:06,511 --> 00:49:09,247
Manager! Why not buy
one of these mackerel cans?

796
00:49:48,619 --> 00:49:52,390
You are… not hurt?

797
00:50:01,699 --> 00:50:04,068
Shirasu, what are you doing?

798
00:50:04,469 --> 00:50:07,805
Manager, it started!

799
00:50:08,072 --> 00:50:10,007
What started?

800
00:50:10,408 --> 00:50:12,677
Unbeknownst to what was going on,

801
00:50:12,844 --> 00:50:17,115
genius realtor Machi Sangenya's head

802
00:50:17,281 --> 00:50:20,585
was occupied with selling houses.

803
00:50:36,467 --> 00:50:38,603
What makes women shine?

804
00:50:38,770 --> 00:50:40,505
We will be participating
in the women's project.

805
00:50:40,671 --> 00:50:42,573
I'm thinking of having her buy this house.

806
00:50:42,740 --> 00:50:44,809
Home is there to raise a child.

807
00:50:44,976 --> 00:50:46,144
It's better to have a child?

808
00:50:46,310 --> 00:50:48,012
-Let's be fair about this.
-I'll accept your challenge.

809
00:50:48,179 --> 00:50:50,915
There is no property I can't sell.
